DEATH: How death works in the Rifts

When your character is killed in combat, what happens depends on
your number of lives remaining (shown in score).

NORMAL DEATH:
  Each death costs one life and 10 percent of your experience.
  You respawn at the Praxis death area. Your equipment and credits
  remain on your corpse at the location where you died.

PERMANENT DEATH:
  When your last life is gone and you are level 4 or above, your
  character is permanently lost. Attempting to log in with that
  name will display a gravestone and the connection will be closed.
  The name remains locked to that character permanently.

  Characters level 3 and below can use the 'suicide' command to
  cleanly delete a character and free the name for reuse.

RECOVERY:
  After a normal death, return to where you died to retrieve your
  corpse. Equipment stored in a dim pocket bag is safe.

